value:
Should I have brought a parasol
too? Mae is always saying the
sun scorches the skin...

On pretty days like this, everyone at
the priory on Novis Island would head
to the shore and share a meal.

You always look so busy... Why don't
you relax a little bit, and spend some
time with me for a change?

Save some room for dessert! I baked
cookies.

How do I look? I dressed up special,
just for our outing. It took a while to
find the right thing to wear!

I was already out and about, so I
thought I'd pay you a little visit!
It's nice to meet you.

That lunch was delicious! I'm full...
of power!
The weather's so nice, isn't it?
Ah, I think I ate too much...

Thanks! We can go on a longer
hike next time.

I'm Genny. Is this where we'll be
picnicking? It's...beautiful!

Phew...I'm tired. I'm not used to
talking so much, but there's just
something about you...$k$pYou see, my mother abandoned me.
I've always wondered why, but lately
I've been thinking about letting it go.$k$pIf she hadn't abandoned me, I never
would have met Celica...or you.$k$pIf I can have days like this, where the
fun seems endless...I can forget my
worries.$k$pI hope we get a chance to talk again.
I really like you. That's our little
secret, OK?
それっ…
たー！
ふええ…
やだあ！
Mind your manners!
Take a marshmallow!
Try some of this?
Feel the breeze!
Food coma…
Ehehe
Pain, pain, go away.
Let me help you.
Look, I made a little doll as a good-luck charm. She's why it's so sunny!
I packed today's lunch, so eat up! There's plenty to go around.
Ooh, flowers! I'll make you a crown. Celica taught me how!
I wonder if my parents ever took me on picnics like this...
This food is so good... You're here... I'm so happy.
(humming a happy little tune)
What great weather...
Here, have a bite.
